ation, this volume seeks to understand and expose the implications of a fundamental problematic: how should scholars and strategists alike understand the contemporary shift from counter-terrorism to counter-extremism?Representing the first collection of scholarly works encountering this present problem of extremism and counter-extremism, this edited volume addresses the need for a critical examination of both the theoretical and the practical implications of this recent conceptual shift. For this very reason, this book brings together a diverse range of scholars, experts and practitioners to present valuable multidisciplinary analyses of the theory and practicalities of countering extremism. It is in this combination of both theoretical investigation and empirical analyses of local realities that the volume finds its added value, offering a unique contribution to a vital field of academic study.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunity development. 0aPolitical violencexPrevention. 0aRadicalismxPrevention. 0aSecurity, International. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  acounter-extremism.  acritical terrorism studies.  aextremism.  agender studies.  apeace studies.  apolitical violence.  apostcolonialism.  apower.  asecurity.  aterrorism.1 aAuchter, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBreen-Smyth, Mariela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuadro, Mariela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDixit, Priya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDramac Jiries, Tanya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernández de Mosteyrín, Laura,